data.title: FSU Football Player of the Week: Dalvin Cook

data.text:
ShareTweet

For Florida State in Week 10, it was another halftime deficit and still, another victory. While sophomore quarterback Jameis Winston overcame to a slow start to put forward perhaps the gutsiest effort of his career by leading the team from behind with a twisted ankle, this week’s Florida State Football Player of the Week goes to a true freshman.

Dalvin Cook takes home the honors after finishing with 150 yards from scrimmage on just 13 touches. Cook finished with 110 yards rushing on just nine carries and 40 yards receiving on four grabs.

Cook found the end zone twice on runs of 40 and 38 yards. His 38-yard touchdown rush with 3:46 to play put the Seminoles ahead for good as FSU overcame an early 21-0 deficit to top Louisville 42-31.

Cook now has 380 yards rushing and five touchdowns for the season. Cook is second on the team in both categories behind only fellow running back Karlos Williams. Florida State will look to improve to 9-0 as it hosts Virginia on Saturday night.

About Mike Ferguson

Mike Ferguson is a Bloguin contributor, the editor of Noled Out and a lifetime Florida State sports enthusiast. Mike vividly remembers watching Warrick Dunn run down the sideline in Gainesville in 1993, the "Choke at Doak" in 1994 and Monte Cummings' driving layup to beat #1 Duke in 2002. Mike has worked as a sports reporter in both print and online. For isportsweb in 2013, Mike gave press coverage of Florida State football's run to the 2013 national championship. Mike has been featured on SI.com, FoxSports.com and Yahoo Sports while interviewing major sports stars such as 2013 National League MVP Andrew McCutchen. Mike graduated from Florida State University in 2009 with a major in Religion and a minor in Communications. Mike currently resides in Haines City, Florida with his wife Jennifer and daughters Trinity and Greenly. Mike is a full-time reporter at Polk County's newspaper, The Ledger, in Lakeland, Florida. Mike can be followed on Twitter @MikeWFerguson.
